ksdk:manifest.brief: This is SDK version 2.5.0 manifest file. It describes the content of the MKL82Z128xxx7 and additional settings for tools that support SDK version 2.5.0

board.name: TWR-KL82Z72M
board.description: TWR-KL82Z72M: Tower System Development Board for Kinetis Ultra-Low-Power KL82 MCUs

specific.content: The TWR-KL82Z72M is a development board for Kinetis KL82 32-bit MCUs. It features the Kinetis MKL82Z128VMC7 MCU 72 MHz ARM® Cortex®-M0+ core, 128 KB flash, 96 KB SCRAM, 121 MAPBGA and USB.The TWR-KL82Z72M operates as a standalone debug tool and can also be combined and used as part of the modular Tower System development platform.

board.name: FRDM-KL82Z
board.description: FRDM-KL82Z: Freedom Development Board for Kinetis Ultra-Low-Power KL82 MCUs

specific.content: The FRDM-KL82Z supports a power supply voltage range of 1.71 to 3.6 V. It features a KL82Z, a device boasting up to 128 KB flash and 96 KB SRAM, and numerous analog and digital peripherals. In addition, the FRDM-KL82Z offers a QSPI interface to expand program memory and USB 2.0 Full Speed without requiring an external crystal.

device.name: MKL82Z7
device.description: KL8x: Kinetis® KL8x-72/96 MHz Secure Ultra-Low Power Microcontrollers (MCUs) based on ARM® Cortex®-M0+ Core

specific.content: The Kinetis® KL8x MCU expands on the Kinetis low-power MCU portfolio with rich security features including tamper detection, true random number generator and low-power trusted crypto engine supporting AES, DES, 3DES, SHA, RSA and ECC.
